T 05. What would you tell a patient calling with an "emergency" situation at this time? Emergency situations could include difficulty breathing, bleeding that won't stop, spinal injury, sudden change in mental state or a head injury with loss of consciousness.[DO NOT READ ANSWER OPTIONS] LISTEN CAREFULLY TO RESPONSE
T  
T Emergency examples:
T - Sudden shortness of breath
T - Fainting or head injury with disorientation
T - Major fracture that breaks the skin
T - Serious Burn
T  
R     A                                                             Hang up dial 911 or go to nearest ER
R     B                                                             Go to an urgent care center
R     C                                                             Will connect caller to a provider or nurse
R     D                                                             Will ask caller to leave their name and number, someone will call them back within 1 hour
R     E                                                             Will provide the caller with phone number to contact their physician or on-call physician or nurse
R     F                                                             Will take caller information and give to the doctor or on-call physician or nurse to call back within 1 hour
R     G                                                             Other (SPECIFY)
R     H                                                             Don't know (DO NOT READ)

